external_knowledge:
- "bloom" metaphorically refers to the start of events;
- "Saturday sun" means the events are scheduled to take place on Saturdays (where '%w' equals '6' in strftime, representing Saturday);
- "reminders that haven't been silenced" means reminders are active (reminder_on_off = 1).

sql:
SELECT events.subject, event_categories.category_name
FROM events
JOIN event_categories ON events.event_category_id = event_categories.event_category_id;

SELECT AVG(num_registrations) as avg_registrations_per_event
FROM (
    SELECT event_id, COUNT(*) as num_registrations
    FROM event_registrations
    GROUP BY event_id
);
